## 2. Eligibility – Who Can Apply

Glassdoor has low formal barriers, and many roles target freshers/students.

Eligible candidates include:
- 11th/12th students (basic content, data entry, marketing support via remote listings)
- First- and second-year undergraduates (entry-level, learning-focused roles)
- Third- and fourth-year students (B.Tech, BCA, B.Com, etc.)
- Final-year and postgraduate students (MCA, MBA, etc.)
- Students with backlogs or gaps (highlight skills honestly; reviews help assess company flexibility)
- Students from smaller towns – use "Remote" or "Work from Home" filters; location is often irrelevant

No strict CGPA cutoffs in most cases; skills, availability, and enthusiasm matter more for beginners.

## 3. Step-by-Step Application Process (Beginner-Friendly)

### 3.1 Profile and Resume Setup

A basic but complete profile helps with applications.

Steps:
1. Sign up or update at https://www.glassdoor.co.in (use personal email; India version recommended).
2. Upload resume: PDF format, simple and keyword-rich (include education, skills like Python, Excel, Canva, and any projects).
3. Complete profile: Add education, skills, summary/objective, and preferences (e.g., "Internship", "Remote", "India").
4. Read company reviews: Search companies first to see ratings, interview difficulty, and stipend insights.

Example summary (beginner):
"First-year student from Maharashtra seeking remote internships in digital marketing or content. Basic knowledge of Canva and social media. Eager to learn and contribute."

### 3.2 Searching for Internships

Main methods:
1. Go to https://www.glassdoor.co.in/Job/index.htm
2. Search keywords: "internship", "intern 2026", "fresher internship", "summer internship 2026", "remote internship"
3. Apply filters:
   - Job type: Internship
   - Location: "Remote" / "Work from Home" / "India"
   - Date posted: Past 7/14 days (fresh listings respond faster)
   - Salary: ₹5,000+ (stipend filter if available)
   - Easy Apply: for quick submissions
4. Sort by: Date (newest first)
5. Set alerts: Enable email notifications for matching searches

Check "2026 batch" or "fresher" tags for beginner roles.

### 3.3 Applying

- "Easy Apply": Upload resume, fill basic details (availability, why interested); many require no cover letter
- Full apply: May redirect to company site; keep answers short and honest
- Customize minimally: Mention remote preference, highlight any self-learning or college activities
- Weekly target: 20–50 applications (focus on fresh postings and remote ones for higher beginner success)

For beginners: Start with "paid internship" or "fresher intern" searches; read reviews to avoid poor experiences.

### 3.4 Interviews and Follow-Up

Most interviews: Phone, video, or simple tasks.
Common questions for beginners:
- Tell me about yourself
- Why this internship?
- Availability (e.g., part-time/full-time)
- Basic skills or projects

Follow up: Check Glassdoor messages/email; send thank-you if possible.

## 4. Strategies by Experience Level (Starting from Beginner)

**Absolute Beginners (Zero Experience):**
- Target content writing, social media, HR support, data entry, marketing roles
- Add free online certs (e.g., Google Digital Marketing) to resume
- Focus on "remote" + "fresher" + "students" listings
- Use reviews to pick supportive companies

**Some Basic Skills/College Projects:**
- Highlight any fest work, Canva designs, or simple projects
- Target ₹8,000–₹20,000 stipends
- Apply to 2026-batch tagged roles

**Advanced/Final Year:**
- Target corporate summer 2026 roles (e.g., Deloitte, Quona)
- Use reviews for PPO potential
- Apply early

## 5. Application Tracking

Use a spreadsheet:
- Date applied
- Company/role
- Stipend (from listing/reviews)
- Application method
- Status
- Follow-up date
- Notes (e.g., review rating)

## 6. Common Reasons for Low Response

- Applying to outdated postings
- Resume missing keywords (e.g., "remote", "fresher")
- Not filtering for remote/beginner roles
- Ignoring company reviews (avoid low-rated ones)

Avoid scams: Never pay fees; apply only through official links.

## 7. Timing and Location Notes

- Early 2026: Summer 2026 internships posting now (apply immediately)
- Peak: February–May for summer roles
- Shirpur/Maharashtra: Prioritize "Remote" / "Work from Home" filters; many nationwide listings are fully remote

## 8. Comparison to Other Platforms

- Internshala: High-volume student roles, custom questions
- LinkedIn: Networking, big brands
- Wellfound: Startup/equity focus
- Indeed: Broad aggregation, easy apply
- Glassdoor: Company reviews + salary transparency, great for beginners evaluating fit

Use multiple platforms for best results.

